radiographic_examinations.findings: The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout with no focal lesions. Gallbladder wall hyperemia and edema with mild distension, stones present within the gallbladder. The pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, uterus and adnexae are within normal limits. No free fluid in the pelvis. No lymphadenopathy or vascular abnormalities. No evidence of osseous lesions or acute fracture with bilateral pars articularis defects and grade 1 anterolisthesis of L5 over S1.
